# Approach
We perform a binary search on the possible answer space by checking whether the given `target` (maximum possible minimum power) is valid or not. For each given `target`, we utilize a sliding window algorithm to check its validity in linear time.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: `O(NlogA)`, where `A` is the range of `[min(stations), sum(stations) + k]`.
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: `O(N)`, for the use of a hashmap to record the addition of new stations temporarily.
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

